Abstract: Repeals provisions regarding a court reporter pool employed by the La. Supreme
Court.
Present law establishes a court reporter pool of 30 court reporters employed by the La.
Supreme Court for assignment to the various district courts.
Present law provides that court reporters in the pool are in addition to all other court
reporters provided for in the district courts. Further provides that the pool court reporters
have the same qualifications, duties, responsibilities, and pay as reporters in a district court.
Present law requires the La. Supreme Court to assign the pool court reporters on a
geographical basis.
Present law provides for an annual salary of $15,000 to pool court reporters to be paid by the
La. Supreme Court from its annual budget. Further limits the travel expenses of pool court
reporters to the amount allowed for other state employees.
